# в–¶пёЏ Notebook Execution Order

| Step | Notebook | Description |
|------|----------|-------------|
| 01 | Data_Generation | Generate sample retail transaction dataset |
| 02 | Bronze_AutoLoader | Incremental ingestion using Databricks Auto Loader |
| 03 | Silver_Layer | Data cleaning, validation and deduplication |
| 04 | Gold_Layer | Business-ready analytics |
| 05 | SQL_Analytics | SQL queries on Bronze, Silver and Gold |
| 06 | Schema_Evolution_Demo | Demonstrate schema evolution |
| 07 | Monitoring | Data quality monitoring |
| 08 | Pipeline_Logs | Pipeline execution logging |
| 09 | Failure_Handling | Failure handling demonstration |
| 10 | Alerting_System | Anomaly detection & Email Notifications |

---

# рџҐ‰ Bronze Layer

Raw ingestion layer.

Features:

- Databricks Auto Loader
- Incremental File Processing
- Checkpointing
- Schema Enforcement
- Ingestion Timestamp
- Delta Lake Storage

---

# рџҐ€ Silver Layer

Data cleansing layer.

Features:

- Remove Null Records
- Remove Duplicate Records
- Data Validation
- Data Standardization
- Clean Delta Table

---

# рџҐ‡ Gold Layer

Business-ready datasets.

Generated KPIs include:

- Top Products
- Top Customers
- Payment Distribution
- Revenue Analysis

---

# рџљЁ Anomaly Detection

The pipeline performs rule-based anomaly detection to identify potential data quality issues.

Examples include:

- Missing critical values
- Invalid quantities
- Invalid prices
- Suspicious transactions

Detected anomalies are included in monitoring reports and execution notifications.

---

# рџ“€ Monitoring & Logging

The project continuously monitors pipeline execution.

Implemented features:

- Pipeline Monitoring
- Data Quality Report
- Execution Status
- Record Counts
- Execution Timestamp
- Pipeline Logs
- Failure Handling

---

# рџ“§ Automated Email Notifications

The pipeline automatically sends an email report after execution.

Each email contains:

- Pipeline Status
- Pipeline Summary
- Total Records
- Good Records
- Anomaly Count
- Execution Timestamp

Emails are sent using Gmail SMTP with App Password authentication.

---

# рџ“Љ SQL Analytics

The Gold layer supports SQL analytics including:

- Revenue Analysis
- Top Customers
- Top Products
- Payment Distribution

